sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Gateway as Gateway (Envoy)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS (service-CA)
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth /<br/>OIDC Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Backend as Backend Service<br/>(via HTTPRoute)

    Note over User,Backend: Flow 1: User Request through Gateway API

    User->>Router: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Router->>Gateway: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS terminate/passthrough
    Gateway->>AuthProxy: ext_authz check<br/>HTTPS/8443 (service-CA)<br/>Cookie: _oauth2_proxy
    AuthProxy->>OAuth: Validate token<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>OAuth2 client credentials
    OAuth-->>AuthProxy: Token valid
    AuthProxy-->>Gateway: Auth OK
    Gateway->>Backend: Forward request<br/>mTLS (DestinationRule)<br/>Bearer Token (Lua inject)
    Backend-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>Router: Response
    Router-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over User,Backend: Flow 2: Component Deployment

    participant Admin as Cluster Admin
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DSCCtrl as DSC Controller
    participant CompCtrl as Component Controller

    Admin->>K8sAPI: Create/Update DSC CR<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>DSCCtrl: Watch event<br/>(in-process)
    DSCCtrl->>CompCtrl: Reconcile component<br/>(in-process)
    CompCtrl->>K8sAPI: Apply kustomize manifests<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>CompCtrl: Resources created

    Note over User,Backend: Flow 3: Platform Monitoring

    participant Prom as Prometheus

    Prom->>AuthProxy: Scrape /metrics<br/>HTTP/9000 plaintext
    AuthProxy-->>Prom: Metrics response
    Prom->>Backend: Scrape ServiceMonitor targets<br/>HTTP/HTTPS varies<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Backend-->>Prom: Metrics response
